What PR-9 does (current final state):
1. Watchdog (Invariant 5): embed_with_watchdog runs each embed on a detached thread; recv_timeout (30s default, configurable) -> RuntimeEmbedderError::Timeout on hang, feeding the existing retry/failure path. Panic-transparent (catch_unwind on the watchdog thread + resume_unwind on the worker so EU-5f ProjectionPanic is unchanged). Cancellation is Invariant-5 "finish + discard".
2. Engine-side embed serialization: embed_serialize: Mutex<()> held by the worker across the embed call (commit/IO stays parallel under commit_gate). Justified on SAFETY (never invoke arbitrary caller-supplied pyo3/napi embedders concurrently); throughput-neutral (candle uses one process-wide rayon pool). Released on timeout so an abandoned embed can't hold it / deadlock the pool; poison-recovered via into_inner.
3. Embed circuit breaker: consecutive_embed_timeouts / embed_circuit_open / embed_circuit_threshold (default 8). Latches after N consecutive watchdog timeouts; once latched, jobs fail fast without embedding -> bounds the abandoned-thread leak (Invariant 5 forbids aborting a running embed). Breaker is checked at job entry, before each retry attempt, AND immediately after acquiring embed_serialize (this last check is the post-pass-3 fix closing the residual spawn window). Counter resets on any returning embed (Ok or typed error).

