   Must be RED before the watchdog exists.
3. Watchdog must **not** false-timeout a legitimately-slow cold embed — add/keep a
   test that a slow-but-under-budget embed (cf. `SleepingEmbedder`) still succeeds.

---

## Codex review focus (call out in the review request)

- The chosen item-1 approach does **not regress projection throughput** (esp. if you
  serialize — show the per-row cost is acceptable).
- The watchdog **cannot false-timeout** a legitimately-slow cold embed.
- If serialization + watchdog coexist: **no lock-poisoning / no deadlock** when an
  embed times out while holding the serialization guard.
- Single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contracts preserved (hard constraint).

---

