     1	//! PR-9 item 1 — engine-side embed serialization.
     2	//!
     3	//! The projection pool runs `PROJECTION_WORKERS` (2) workers. PR-9 serializes
     4	//! the embed *call* engine-side so the shared `Arc<dyn Embedder>` is invoked
     5	//! by at most one worker at a time, while commit/IO stays parallel.
     6	//!
     7	//! Rationale is SAFETY, not throughput: the engine accepts arbitrary
     8	//! caller-supplied embedders (pyo3 / napi bridges) that are `Sync` only by
     9	//! contract and may not be truly concurrency-safe; serializing engine-side
    10	//! makes the projection robust to them. (Throughput is ~neutral — candle
    11	//! fans every forward onto one process-wide rayon pool, so concurrent
    12	//! forwards share it rather than getting 2x; the PR-9 pre-flight also
    13	//! confirmed concurrent CandleBge embeds neither wedge nor corrupt.)
