## Verdict: BLOCK

### 1. [blocker] Breaker bounds only consecutive timeouts, not total abandoned embed threads
Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:225), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:236), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3598), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3601), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3618), [pr9_embed_watchdog.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr9_embed_watchdog.rs:224)

`consecutive_embed_timeouts` is reset by any later returning embed, even though previously timed-out detached threads are still alive. That means an embedder that hangs on some inputs but returns `Ok` or typed errors on others can leak one abandoned thread per timed-out call indefinitely and never latch the breaker. The timeout-path lock release was only safe because the breaker was supposed to cap that leak; as implemented, it only caps the persistently-all-timeout case, and the test suite covers only that narrower case.

### 2. [low] A few comments still overstate the behavior after PR-9
Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:75), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:76), [pr9_concurrent_embed.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr9_concurrent_embed.rs:116), [pr9_concurrent_embed.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr9_concurrent_embed.rs:137)

The threshold comment says the breaker “bounds” the leak and that a legitimate embed “never approaches” 30s; both are stronger than the current design justifies. The long-seed test still says the two workers “concurrently embed throughout” and discusses a “healthy unserialized seed,” but this PR serializes embeds engine-side.

**What passed on inspection**
- The new post-lock breaker re-check is correctly placed; a worker queued on `embed_serialize` now bails before spawning another watchdog thread.
- Panic propagation before the deadline is intact: `resume_unwind` still feeds the existing EU-5f `ProjectionPanic` path, and commit work remains outside the embed mutex under `commit_gate`.
- The timeout path does not wedge the pool on mutex poisoning or lock retention; `embed_serialize` is recovered with `into_inner`, and timed-out calls do free the guard.
- The new watchdog tests are honest for the cases they actually exercise, and the breaker test does hit the retry path via non-empty retry delays.

**Reviewer process notes**
- Reviewed the current [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1) diff, all four new PR-9 tests, [ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol.md](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol.md:100), the PR-9 prompt, the consolidated prior verdict, and the closure artifact.
- Read-only sandbox: no edits, no verdict file write, no local test execution.
- The repo-local `MEMORY.md` referenced by `AGENTS.md` is not present in this checkout; only a sibling-project memory file exists and is unrelated.
